opened.title: Agent is reposting images from other parts of conversation as its own image
opened.body: For some reason, on Twitter, the agent will respond with an image which is a respost of images from other conversation it has had. This is clearly a bug. If it generates an image, that's cool, but it seems to be sending the old image.

opened.title: Fix queueing in Twitter so messages are not rate limited constantly
opened.body: The way we are queueing messages is very shoddy and causes rate limiting.

opened.title: Fix Twitter Multi-agent, Characters respond to each other's messages
opened.body:
Right now if we run two agents at the same time, only one responds on twitter and uses the personality of the other agent.

We need to make sure that this is not happening, and that each responds on their own.

opened.title: Allow twitter client to configure who to reply to based on following relationship
opened.body:
It would be good to allow agent owners to be able to turn on/off who their twitter agents reply to.

Preference is to just reply to accounts the agent is following.

This will reduce spam and allow agent owners to have a bit more control over interactions.


**Additional context**
Probably related to https://github.com/ai16z/eliza/issues/259
